theorem frontier_frontier_subset_frontier {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    frontier (frontier A) ⊆ frontier A := by
  intro x hx
  -- `hx` gives `x ∈ closure (frontier A)`
  have hx_closure : x ∈ closure (frontier A) := hx.1
  -- Since `frontier A ⊆ closure A`, we have `closure (frontier A) ⊆ closure A`
  have hx_closureA : x ∈ closure A := by
    have h_sub : frontier A ⊆ closure A :=
      frontier_subset_closure (A := A)
    have h_closure_sub : closure (frontier A) ⊆ closure A :=
      closure_mono h_sub
    exact h_closure_sub hx_closure
  -- Show that `x ∉ interior A`
  have hx_not_intA : x ∉ interior A := by
    intro hx_intA
    -- The neighbourhood `interior A` must meet `frontier A` (by closure property)
    have h_nonempty :
        (interior A ∩ frontier A).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hx_closure (interior A) isOpen_interior hx_intA
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, hy_intA, hy_frontierA⟩
    -- But `frontier A` is disjoint from `interior A`
    have : y ∉ interior A :=
      (frontier_subset_compl_interior (A := A)) hy_frontierA
    exact this hy_intA
  -- Combine the two facts to obtain `x ∈ frontier A`
  exact And.intro hx_closureA hx_not_intA

theorem fixed_frontier_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :

  exact hx.1

theorem P3_union_open {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 A → IsOpen B → Topology.P3 (A ∪ B) := by
  intro hP3A hOpenB
  have hP3B : Topology.P3 B := Topology.isOpen_P3 (A := B) hOpenB
  exact Topology.P3_union (A := A) (B := B) hP3A hP3B
